WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.666 --> 00:00:03.406
<v ->We've all heard of the profiteering involved in war.</v>

2
00:00:03.406 --> 00:00:06.986
In short, war is good business for those in the power elite.

3
00:00:06.986 --> 00:00:09.006
The war in Irag is no exception.

4
00:00:09.006 --> 00:00:11.286
Film producer, Robert Greenwald has pulled together

5
00:00:11.286 --> 00:00:13.906
a portrait of the degree to which this war

6
00:00:13.906 --> 00:00:15.546
has been conducted to profit those

7
00:00:15.546 --> 00:00:19.426
closest to those in power and the profits are staggering.

8
00:00:19.426 --> 00:00:22.226
Try the $45 per six-pack of coke

9
00:00:22.226 --> 00:00:24.486
the government pays the services contractor

10
00:00:24.486 --> 00:00:28.106
or the $100 to do a load of the soldiers skivvies

11
00:00:28.106 --> 00:00:30.386
and that's only small potatoes compared to the rest

12
00:00:30.386 --> 00:00:33.522
of what's detailed in the film "Iraq for Sale".

13
00:00:33.522 --> 00:00:38.372 line:15% 
(rhythmic music)

14
00:00:42.154 --> 00:00:43.980
What prompted you to tell this story?

15
00:00:45.270 --> 00:00:48.006
<v ->A friend of mine suggested that war profiteering</v>

16
00:00:48.006 --> 00:00:51.846
was one of the great uncovered stories and he felt

17
00:00:51.846 --> 00:00:55.406
that if we could do the movie and do it reasonably quickly,

18
00:00:55.406 --> 00:00:58.886
come the fall, when we're in the election campaign,

19
00:00:58.886 --> 00:01:00.996
we could use the film to force a

20
00:01:00.996 --> 00:01:03.597
debate about war profiteering.

21
00:01:03.597 --> 00:01:04.816
This was in January.

22
00:01:04.816 --> 00:01:07.075
It's now September and we were able to get it done

23
00:01:07.075 --> 00:01:11.092
on an insane schedule and hopefully, now,

24
00:01:11.092 --> 00:01:14.092
it's doing what it needs to do, which is people

25
00:01:14.092 --> 00:01:17.192
are taking it, they're screening it, they're organizing it,

26
00:01:17.192 --> 00:01:20.692
and they're using it to ask questions about

27
00:01:20.692 --> 00:01:23.332
what's going on with war profiteering,

28
00:01:23.332 --> 00:01:26.202
who's protecting me, and who's not protecting me.

29
00:01:27.542 --> 00:01:29.159
<v Regina>If we can get into a little bit,</v>

30
00:01:29.159 --> 00:01:33.296
how did this story, what revealed itself to you in the

31
00:01:33.296 --> 00:01:35.270
process of researching this subject,

32
00:01:35.270 --> 00:01:37.501
and get into the meat and bones of it little bit.

33
00:01:38.631 --> 00:01:41.602
<v ->As we started the research, I was sure that</v>

34
00:01:41.602 --> 00:01:45.822
there would be some troubling facts and figures.

35
00:01:45.822 --> 00:01:50.122
What I didn't really focus on is that profiteering

36
00:01:50.122 --> 00:01:53.842
is not a victimless crime, it's not a white-collar crime,

37
00:01:53.842 --> 00:01:56.302
which kind of just goes out into the environment

38
00:01:56.302 --> 00:01:59.243
and you don't know how it's affecting anybody.

39
00:01:59.243 --> 00:02:01.902
People's lives are being lost and in the movie,

40
00:02:01.902 --> 00:02:04.082
we have truck drivers whose best friends

41
00:02:04.082 --> 00:02:07.580
were killed in Iraq because Halliburton

42
00:02:07.580 --> 00:02:11.281
was cutting corners to make a bigger profit.

43
00:02:11.281 --> 00:02:14.020
The head of Halliburton has made over $100,000,000

44
00:02:14.020 --> 00:02:16.719
in his stock since the war began.

45
00:02:16.719 --> 00:02:19.620
We have mothers whose sons were killed at Fallujah

46
00:02:19.620 --> 00:02:23.298
because Blackwater was trying to save money

47
00:02:23.298 --> 00:02:25.758
and doing things they shouldn't have done,

48
