99
00:05:03.890 --> 00:05:06.988
<v ->What it means is that whatever the cost is</v>

100
00:05:06.988 --> 00:05:11.818
Halliburton gets that money, plus a built-in profit

101
00:05:11.818 --> 00:05:15.626
based on the size of the contract, which means

102
00:05:15.626 --> 00:05:18.346
the more you spend, the more profit you make

103
00:05:18.346 --> 00:05:22.346
so there's absolutely no inducement or incentive

104
00:05:22.346 --> 00:05:24.686
or reason for them to spend less.

105
00:05:24.686 --> 00:05:26.766
In fact, there's reason to spend more.

106
00:05:26.766 --> 00:05:27.926
<v Regina>So how would you cost-plus</v>

107
00:05:27.926 --> 00:05:30.946
a six-pack of Coke up to $45?

108
00:05:32.516 --> 00:05:36.190
