What's the story they're told,

117
00:05:54.284 --> 00:05:58.317
while they're still here, before they go to Iraq?

118
00:05:58.317 --> 00:05:59.356
<v ->First of all, they're told they'll</v>

119
00:05:59.356 --> 00:06:00.854
be safe or they have been told.

120
00:06:00.854 --> 00:06:03.184
One of the reasons I hope the people will screen the film

121
00:06:03.184 --> 00:06:06.151
all over is we have to break that mythology down.

122
00:06:06.151 --> 00:06:08.452
People have to know how dangerous it is

123
00:06:08.452 --> 00:06:11.152
and second of all, we are at a time in the United States

124
00:06:11.152 --> 00:06:14.441
where it's tragic, but a truck driver has to go to Iraq

125
00:06:14.441 --> 00:06:17.768
to make a living to pay for his healthcare or

126
00:06:17.768 --> 00:06:19.868
to put his children through school.

127
00:06:19.868 --> 00:06:23.909
That's a tragedy of the worst kind and again,

128
00:06:23.909 --> 00:06:27.349
like in the Walmart movie, we're looking at a system.

129
00:06:27.349 --> 00:06:29.769
We're not looking at individual crooks.

130
00:06:29.769 --> 00:06:32.108
We're looking at a system of profit,

131
00:06:32.108 --> 00:06:36.268
large corporations that give money to politicians

132
00:06:36.268 --> 00:06:39.889
that hire former high-level military and politicians,

133
00:06:39.889 --> 00:06:43.988
and as a result, are getting significant contracts

134
00:06:43.988 --> 00:06:47.629
and making millions and ultimately billions of dollars.

135
00:06:47.629 --> 00:06:50.068
<v Regina>So how much are they offering</v>

136
00:06:50.068 --> 00:06:52.288
to these people to do a truck driving job?

137
00:06:52.288 --> 00:06:54.068
I assume it's for a Tour of Duty,

138
00:06:54.068 --> 00:06:56.168
for a few months or a set period of time.

139
00:06:56.168 --> 00:06:57.168
<v ->It's variable.</v>

140
00:06:57.168 --> 00:06:58.687
It depends on what trucks you're in,

